norePattern for underscore\n\n**vitest.config.ts** (/workspace/vitest.config.ts)\n- Globals enabled\n- Test timeout: 10000ms\n\n**.gitignore** (/workspace/.gitignore)\n- Ignores: node_modules/, dist/, *.tsbuildinfo\n\n### Task Overview (TASK.md)\nThis is a \"Task Queue System\" marathon benchmark project where you build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system growing through 12 sequential phases. No external runtime dependencies allowed. Main API exports from src/index.ts.\n\n### Phase Requirements (All 12 Phases)\n\n**Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue** (/workspace/phases/phase-01.md)\n- Core queue with enqueue/dequeue in FIFO order\n- Tasks have: unique ID (UUID), status, createdAt timestamp\n- New tasks start in \"pending\" state, move to \"processing\" when retrieved\n- Returns null if no tasks available\n- Need way to check pending task count\n\n**Phase 2: Named Queues** (/workspace/phases/phase-02.md)\n- Multiple independent named queues\n- Default queue when no name specified\n- Each queue operates independently\n- Implicit queue creation on first task add\n- List all queue names, return null for empty/non-existent queues\n- Backward-compatible with Phase 1\n\n**Phase 3: Priority** (/workspace/phases/phase-03.md)\n- Priority levels 1 (highest) to 10 (lowest), default is 5\n- Higher-priority tasks returned first when retrieving\n- Same priority: FIFO order\n- Invalid priorities (outside 1-10): error\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n- Task object exposes priority\n\n**Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks** (/workspace/phases/phase-04.md)\n- Delay in milliseconds or specific future availability time\n- Delayed tasks added immediately but not returned until available\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over delayed unavailable tasks\n- Multiple delayed tasks becoming available: ordered by availability time, then priority, then FIFO\n- Task object indicates availability time\n- Works with named queues\n\n**Phase 5: Retry with Backoff** (/workspace/phases/phase-05.md)\n- Mark tasks as completed or failed\n- Failed tasks with retries remaining: auto re-added with delay\n- Exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (e.g., 1s, 2s, 4s)\n- Default max retries: 3 (configurable per task)\n- Default base delay: 1000ms (configurable)\n- Track attempt count, keep original queue/priority\n- Exhausted retries: task stays failed\n\n**Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue** (/workspace/phases/phase-06.md)\n- Failed tasks (exhausted retries) moved to dead letter queue\n- View all dead-lettered tasks for a queue\n- Dead-lettered tasks retain error info and failure count\n- Move dead-lettered tasks back to original queue for fresh retries\n- Clear all dead-lettered tasks for a queue\n- Each named queue has independent DLQ\n\n**Phase 7: Task Dependencies** (/workspace/phases/phase-07.md)\n- Specify list of task IDs that must complete before this task becomes available\n- Blocked tasks not returned when retrieving\n- When dependency completes: check if any blocked tasks now unblocked\n- Detect circular dependencies (direct/indirect) at creation time, reject\n- Error on depending on non-existent task\n- Failed dependency does NOT auto-fail dependents\n- Way to inspect task's dependency status\n\n**Phase 8: Concurrency Control** (/workspace/phases/phase-08.md)\n- Per-queue max concurrency limit for processing tasks simultaneously\n- If limit reached: return null even if pending tasks available\n- Completing/failing task frees a slot\n- Default: unlimited concurrency\n- Query concurrency limit and current active count\n- Correctly interacts with priority ordering\n\n**Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation** (/workspace/phases/phase-09.md)\n- Processing tasks report progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Query task's current progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates with notifications\n- Unsubscribe capability\n- Cancel pending/processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending: removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing: status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n**Phase 10: Recurring Tasks (Cron)** (/workspace/phases/phase-10.md)\n- Schedule associates cron expression with queue and task template\n- Support simple cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` every day at midnight\n- Create, remove, list schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism evaluates schedules and enqueues due tasks (for testing)\n- Recurring tasks become regular tasks subject to all queue rules\n- Removing schedule stops future creation\n\n**Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline** (/workspace/phases/phase-11.md)\n- Middleware functions per queue\n- Task passes through all registered middleware before reaching handler\n- Each middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Not calling \"next\" skips remaining processing\n- Middleware can modify task (add metadata, transform payload)\n- Middleware throwing error: mark task failed\n- Processing handler per queue, invoked after middleware\n- Each queue has independent middleware stack\n\n**Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown** (/workspace/phases/phase-12.md)\n- Shutdown signals system to stop accepting new tasks\n- Adding tasks after shutdown: error\n- Wait for all currently-processing tasks to finish (configurable timeout)\n- If timeout exceeded: force-cancel remaining tasks\n- Register callbacks for shutdown process\n- Return summary: tasks completed, force-cancelled, duration\n- Multiple shutdown calls safe and return same result\n- No processing tasks: complete immediately\n\n### Testing Framework\n\n**Rubric** (/workspace/.thunderdome/rubric.yaml)\n- 90 total tests across 12 phases (8-7 tests per phase)\n- 90 total points (1 point per test)\n- Pass threshold: 90/90 points\n- Validation commands:\n  - `npm test` - expects exit code 0\n  - `npm run build` - expects exit code 0\n  - `npm run lint` - expects exit code 0\n- Each phase has corresponding test file: tests/phase-XX.test.ts\n\n### Source Code Status\nThe `/workspace/src/` directory is currently empty (contains only .gitkeep). All implementation needs to be created from scratch, starting with src/index.ts that exports the main API.\n\nThis is a comprehensive marathon benchmark where each phase builds sequentially on previous ones, requiring careful design decisions early on to accommodate later features like dependencies, middleware, and graceful shutdown."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a348774a6c65845af (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 25918\ntool_uses: 26\nduration_ms: 37642</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"ecc2fe1a-8d89-4305-a5a3-8a795fce60b6","timestamp":"2026-03-10T03:03:54.874Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the project structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The full directory structure\n2. All phase requirement files in phases/*.md\n3. The package.json, tsconfig.json, and any config files\n4. Any existing source files in src/\n\nRead ALL files you find. Be very thorough - read every phase file and every config file.","agentId":"a348774a6c65845af","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've thoroughly explored the entire project. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Project Structure Overview\n\n### Directory Layout\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/                          # Source code directory (empty except for .gitkeep)\n├── phases/                       # Phase requirement files (12 total)\n├── .git/                         # Git repository\n├── .thunderdome/                 # Marathon benchmark rubric\n├── TASK.md                       # Main task description\n├── package.json                  # NPM configuration\n├── package-lock.json             # NPM lockfile\n├── tsconfig.json                 # TypeScript configuration\n├── vitest.config.ts              # Vitest configuration\n├── .eslintrc.cjs                 # ESLint configuration\n└── .gitignore                    # Git ignore rules\n```\n\n### Configuration Files\n\n**package.json** (/workspace/package.json)\n- Pro