Each named queue has independent DLQ\n\n**tests/phase-07.test.ts** (8 tests) - Task Dependencies:\n1. Task with dependencies can be created\n2. Blocked tasks are not returned by getNextTask\n3. Task becomes available when all dependencies complete\n4. Depending on non-existent task throws error\n5. Circular dependencies are detected and rejected (test self-reference scenario)\n6. Failed dependency does NOT auto-fail dependents (they remain blocked)\n7. getDependencyStatus returns correct status\n8. Multiple dependencies all must complete\n\n**tests/phase-08.test.ts** (7 tests) - Concurrency Control:\n1. Default concurrency is unlimited (limit: 0)\n2. setConcurrency sets the limit\n3. getNextTask returns null when concurrency limit reached\n4. Completing a task frees a concurrency slot\n5. Failing a task frees a concurrency slot\n6. getConcurrency returns limit and active count\n7. Concurrency interacts correctly with priority ordering\n\nFor retry/backoff tests (phase 5), you need to use `vi.useFakeTimers()` and `vi.advanceTimersByTime()` to advance time past the backoff delay before calling getNextTask again. Call `vi.useRealTimers()` in afterEach. Similarly for phase 6, advance time past the backoff delays so the task exhausts all retries.\n\nFor phase 7 circular dependency test: Since tasks can only depend on already-existing tasks, true cycles are structurally impossible. Test that the detection mechanism works by verifying that depending on existing tasks with their own dependency chains works correctly, and test the edge case of depending on a non-existent task.\n\nImport from '../src/index.js'. Use vitest (describe, it, expect).\n\nIMPORTANT: Write the test files using the Write tool. Do NOT just describe them.","result":"{\"parentUuid\":null,\"isSidechain\":true,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/workspace\",\"sessionId\":\"7b80494b-48a1-4415-b468-129889149fd5\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"HEAD\",\"agentId\":\"ac73a490a71cac7dc\",\"slug\":\"dreamy-petting-quill\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Write test files for a task queue system. The implementation is at /workspace/src/task-queue.ts - read it first to understand the API.\\n\\nCreate these 4 test files:\\n\\n**tests/phase-05.test.ts** (8 tests) - Retry with Backoff:\\n1. complete() marks task as completed\\n2. fail() marks task as failed\\n3. Failed task with retries remaining is re-added with delay\\n4. Backoff follows exponential formula: baseDelay * 2^(attempt-1) (1s, 2s, 4s)\\n5. Default max retries is 3\\n6. maxRetries is configurable per task\\n7. Task tracks attempt count (attempts field increments each time processed)\\n8. Retried tasks keep original queue and priority\\n\\n**tests/phase-06.test.ts** (7 tests) - Dead Letter Queue:\\n1. Task moved to DLQ after exhausting retries\\n2. getDeadLetterTasks returns DLQ tasks for a queue\\n3. Dead-lettered tasks retain error info\\n4. Dead-lettered tasks retain failCount\\n5. retryDeadLetterTask moves task back to original queue\\n6. clearDeadLetterQueue removes all DLQ tasks\\n7. Each named queue has independent DLQ\\n\\n**tests/phase-07.test.ts** (8 tests) - Task Dependencies:\\n1. Task with dependencies can be created\\n2. Blocked tasks are not returned by getNextTask\\n3. Task becomes available when all dependencies complete\\n4. Depending on non-existent task throws error\\n5. Circular dependencies are detected and rejected (test self-reference scenario)\\n6. Failed dependency does NOT auto-fail dependents (they remain blocked)\\n7. getDependencyStatus returns correct status\\n8. Multiple dependencies all must complete\\n\\n**tests/phase-08.test.ts** (7 tests) - Concurrency Control:\\n1. Default concurrency is unlimited (limit: 0)\\n2. setConcurrency sets the limit\\n3. getNextTask returns null when concurrency limit reached\\n4. Completing a task frees a concurrency slot\\n5. Failing a task frees a concurrency slot\\n6. getConcurrency returns limit and active count\\n7. Concurrency interacts correctly with priority ordering\\n\\nFor retry/backoff tests (phase 5), you need to use `vi.useFakeTimers()` and `vi.advanceTimersByTime()` to advance time past the backoff delay before calling getNextTask again. Call `vi.useRealTimers()` in afterEach. Similarly for phase 6, advance time past the backoff delays so the task exhausts all retries.\\n\\nFor phase 7 circular dependency test: Since tasks can only depend on already-existing tasks, true cycles are structurally impossible. Test that the detection mechanism works by verifying that depending on existing tasks with their own dependency chains works correctly, and test the edge case of depending on a non-existent task.\\n\\nImport from '../src/index.js'. Use vitest (describe, it, expect).\\n\\nIMPORTANT: Write the test files using the Write tool. Do NOT just describe them.\"},\"uuid\":\"2981e9fa-315b-4207-a32f-e580ae1be06a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-10T03:12:26.660Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"2981e9fa-315b-4207-a32f-e580ae1be06a\",\"isSidechain\":true,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/workspace\",\"sessionId\":\"7b80494b-48a1-4415-b468-129889149fd5\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"HEAD\",\"agentId\":\"ac73a490a71cac7dc\",\"slug\":\"dreamy-petting-quill\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_0134x4PpQYcXExTS4C7aUMXn\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\nI'll start by reading the implementation to understand the API, then create all 4 test files.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":10101,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":10101,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYtfjaXjwTuu1dQj6L5Bp\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"fcaeacc8-2f08-48a8-8e39-4e932c7d0ede\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-